## STEP 5 — Frontend Architecture

### Recommended Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| **Framework** | Expo 55 + Expo Router | Already set up; supports web + iOS + Android |
| **Language** | TypeScript (strict) | Type safety aligned with backend Zod schemas |
| **State Management** | Zustand | Lightweight, minimal boilerplate, React Native friendly |
| **Server State** | TanStack React Query v5 | Caching, auto-refetch, optimistic updates, infinite scroll |
| **HTTP Client** | Custom `fetch` wrapper | Handles auth headers, token refresh, error normalization |
| **Forms** | React Hook Form + Zod | Validates against same schemas as backend |
| **Charts** | `react-native-gifted-charts` or `victory-native` | Cross-platform charting |
| **Auth** | `@supabase/supabase-js` | Direct Supabase Auth integration |
| **Storage** | `expo-secure-store` | Secure token persistence |

