## STEP 8 — Mobile Compatibility Strategy

### Responsive Layout

| Strategy | Implementation |
|----------|---------------|
| **Expo Router** | Single codebase renders on iOS, Android, and Web |
| **Platform-specific files** | [.web.tsx](file:///d:/2026%20Projects/trackifi-mobile/src/components/app-tabs.web.tsx) / `.native.tsx` suffix for divergent UI (already used in project) |
| **Flex layout** | React Native `Flexbox` for all layouts (no CSS Grid needed) |
| **Safe areas** | `react-native-safe-area-context` for notch/inset handling |
| **Bottom sheet** | `@gorhom/bottom-sheet` on native, CSS bottom drawers on web |

### Shared Design Tokens

All design tokens (colors, spacing, typography, radii) defined in `src/constants/tokens.ts` and consumed via `useTheme()` hook. Tokens are **platform-agnostic** — no CSS variables on native, no `StyleSheet` on web (handled via [.web.tsx](file:///d:/2026%20Projects/trackifi-mobile/src/components/app-tabs.web.tsx) variants).

### API Contract Consistency

- Same TypeScript types in `src/types/` used by both web and mobile
- API client auto-attaches auth headers regardless of platform
- Token storage differs: `expo-secure-store` (native) vs `localStorage` (web)

### Future React Native / Flutter Reuse

| Reusable Layer | How |
|----------------|-----|
| Types (`src/types/`) | Copy directly to any TS-based client |
| API service (`src/services/`) | Replace `fetch` with platform HTTP client |
| Business logic / utils | Framework-agnostic, pure functions |
| Design tokens | Export as JSON for Flutter `ThemeData` |

